headline: AIG Q2 Deep Dive: Strategic Shifts and Expense Discipline Amid Softening Property Market
summary: Global insurance giant AIG (NYSE:AIG) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 4.3% year on year to $6.84 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.81 per share was 13.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
